The paper deals with the problem of computing a function over a directed acyclic network, which is a topic in the field of information theory (cs.IT). The use of variable length network codes and in-network compression suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of networked systems (cs.NI). The study of computation capacity and entropy is also relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) due to its focus on network computation. Finally, the use of upper and lower bounds suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC).
